From: Petr Wozniak <petr.wozniak@gmail.com>
Subject: [PATCH] wifi: mt76: mt7996: register a LED classdev for every band

On MT7996 the per-band LED callbacks (brightness_set/blink_set) were only
assigned to the primary PHY (dev->mphy, the 2.4 GHz band) in
mt7996_init_wiphy(). The extra bands (5 GHz / 6 GHz) are brought up later
through mt7996_register_phy() -> mt7996_init_wiphy_band(), which never set
those callbacks, so mt76_led_init() bailed out early for them and only
mt76-phy0 was ever registered.

Under the single-wiphy MLO model used by MT7996 this means the 5/6 GHz LEDs
can never be controlled: the 2.4 GHz LED works while the 5/6 GHz LEDs stay
dark, as reported for a long time on BE14-based cards.

The hardware path is already per band: mt7996_led_set_config() indexes
MT_LED_EN()/MT_LED_CTRL()/MT_LED_TX_BLINK() by mphy->band_idx and even has
dedicated MT_LED_CTRL_BLINK_BAND_SEL handling for MT_BAND1, so per-band
hardware TX-blink works as soon as the classdev exists.

Move the LED callback assignment into mt7996_init_wiphy_band(), which runs
for every band (primary and the mt7996_register_phy() ones), so a LED
classdev (mt76-phy0/1/2) is registered for each band.

Signed-off-by: Petr Wozniak <petr.wozniak@gmail.com>
---
 mt7996/init.c | 17 ++++++++++++-----
 1 file changed, 12 insertions(+), 5 deletions(-)

--- a/mt7996/init.c
+++ b/mt7996/init.c
@@ -545,6 +545,17 @@
 	mt7996_set_stream_vht_txbf_caps(phy);
 	mt7996_set_stream_he_eht_caps(phy);
 	mt7996_init_txpower(phy);
+
+	/* Register a LED classdev for every band, not only the first one.
+	 * Under single-wiphy MLO the 5/6 GHz bands come up via
+	 * mt7996_register_phy(); without these callbacks mt76_led_init()
+	 * skips them and only the 2.4 GHz LED is exposed. The hardware
+	 * TX-blink path is already indexed by band_idx, so per-band blink
+	 * works once the classdev exists. */
+	if (IS_ENABLED(CONFIG_MT76_LEDS)) {
+		phy->mt76->leds.cdev.brightness_set = mt7996_led_set_brightness;
+		phy->mt76->leds.cdev.blink_set = mt7996_led_set_blink;
+	}
 }
 
 static void
@@ -623,12 +634,6 @@
 	hw->max_tx_fragments = 4;
 	wiphy->txq_memory_limit = 32 << 20; /* 32 MiB */
 
-	/* init led callbacks */
-	if (IS_ENABLED(CONFIG_MT76_LEDS)) {
-		dev->mphy.leds.cdev.brightness_set = mt7996_led_set_brightness;
-		dev->mphy.leds.cdev.blink_set = mt7996_led_set_blink;
-	}
-
 	wiphy->max_scan_ssids = 4;
 	wiphy->max_scan_ie_len = IEEE80211_MAX_DATA_LEN;
 
